From c4c2c4f6e6eccf2c498137c2484145900adbe097 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 04:01:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix notification dedup (#4) and replace DOM-string Alexa
 trigger (#3)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

#4 - Notification dedup + pagination guard:
- Add notificationsRef to mirror state so the chemistry alert effect
  can check for existing unread alerts without a stale closure.
- Cap the in-memory notification list at 30 entries.
- Prevents infinite loop that would occur if notifications were added
  as a dependency of the chemistry useEffect.

#3 - Replace DOM getElementById Alexa webhook trigger:
- AlexaSandbox now accepts onRegisterTrigger prop and calls it on
  mount with its own handleSendCommand function.
- App.tsx stores the reference in alexaSandboxCommandRef via
  handleAlexaWebhookTrigger callback.
- AlexaConnectionManager calls the callback directly — no more
  getElementById, synthetic input events, or setTimeout clicks.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01HcLwaFBJUVmjGnMpGbKorB
